This paper is about evaluating the retrieval effectiveness of web search engines, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of crowdsourcing and specialised software, which could be related to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper discusses the types of queries used in the study, which could be related to Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as these fields often deal with natural language processing and information security, respectively.
